Citation.sTitle: Thermodynamic Properties of Inorganic Salts in Nonaqueous Solvents. V. Apparent Molar Volumes and Compressibilities of Divalent Transition Metal Bromides in N,N-Dimethylformamide
Citation.sAbstract: Densities at (283.15, 293.15, 298.15, 303.15, 313.15, 323.15, and 333.15) K and sound velocities at 298.15 K of divalent transition metal bromides in N,N-dimethylformamide have been measured. From these data, apparent molar volumes and apparent molar isentropic compressibilities have been evaluated. The results have been discussed in terms of complex formation.
